To translate and execute a simple program using shell commands, follow these steps:
1) Open a command prompt (or terminal).
2) Change directories to where you want to store your source code file. For example: `cd c:\exercise\ipro`
3) Create a new text file for the source code using Notepad or Notepad++, and save it as 'test.c'.
4) Enter the following code in the test.c text file:
```c
#include <stdio.h>
int main(void) {
   int x,y;
   printf("Enter two integers: ");
   scanf("%d %d", &x, &y);
   if (x>y) { 
      printf("%d\n", x);
   } else {
      printf("%d\n", y);
   }
   return 0;
}
```
5) Compile the source code using GCC with the appropriate options: `gcc -std=c11 -pedantic-errors -Wall -o test.exe test.c`
6) Execute the compiled program: `test

